Amid the global outreach on Operation Sindoor to rally support for India’s war against terror, Congress MP Shashi Tharoor Friday expressed disappointment over the Colombian government’s “heartfelt condolences over the loss of lives in Pakistan, rather than sympathising with the victims of terror”.

“Colombian government, which apparently expressed heartfelt condolences on the loss of lives in Pakistan after the Indian strikes, rather than sympathising with the victims of terrorism. We will say to our friends in Colombia, there can be no equivalance between those who dispatch terrorists and those who resist them,” Tharoor, who is leading an all-party delegation, said in Bogotá.
